    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-4809584">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-4809584">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4809584)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4809584">
																		+1
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greyzor" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6932693); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6932693&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610224711" alt="Greyzor" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6932693)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greyzor" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6932693); return false;" >Greyzor</a></span> <span class="odate time_1604312019 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Nov 2020 10:13</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4809584">
									

<p>Thank you, Team RR, for bringing my favorite canon out of hybernation! It has been really uplifting to see more great authors devoted to it.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;I&nbsp;totally&nbsp;liked&nbsp;your&nbsp;approach&nbsp;to&nbsp;Resurrection:&nbsp;Old&nbsp;Foes.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;I&nbsp;totally&nbsp;liked&nbsp;your&nbsp;approach&nbsp;to&nbsp;Resurrection:&nbsp;Old&nbsp;Foes.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>A view from outside the organization, not having to deal with all the vicissitudes of the main Resurrection, but building on it. Something that was actually missing and begging to be in is the enemy. In that regard, I only wish you would have explained the <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/immediate-actions">first attack of soldiers in black</a>, which started it all, but still remains a mystery.<br />
I can also see why you did not include GOC to ally with Bowe. The Foundation would have had major difficulties, the amount of writing in this war would have been huge, and lots of SCP’s would have likely remained in their cells and without attention. Decontainment has coped with that task without having to write 500 pages of lore. Your team also ditched the whole Sons of Bowe and Abigale Mary Bowe stuff for the same reasons, but here, I am not so sure. It would have been interesting to see where she was going and where’d she end up.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Thumbs&nbsp;up&nbsp;for&nbsp;incorporation&nbsp;of&nbsp;tens&nbsp;of&nbsp;significant&nbsp;SCPs,&nbsp;both&nbsp;old&nbsp;and&nbsp;new.&nbsp;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Thumbs&nbsp;up&nbsp;for&nbsp;incorporation&nbsp;of&nbsp;tens&nbsp;of&nbsp;significant&nbsp;SCPs,&nbsp;both&nbsp;old&nbsp;and&nbsp;new.&nbsp;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Holy hell, we know even 10% of Site-19 SCPs could have led to all types of K-class scenarios, but how gracefully did you justify Bowe’s goals not to inflict damage upon humanity, but rather change the Foundation. That makes the work of Dan and all of Foundation assets really believable.<br />
Loved the involvement of Cassy, the backstory of 096, 140, and even Procrastinati. 682 with 035 could only have that kind of pacifier, too. 2994 made me read the whole Decommission series again, hats off to you guys for thinking that through. Somewhere in the end of Part 1, I understood that I am still too early to consider myself a real geek of SCP. The combinations you did with these numerous objects have almost made my head ache, which is why I am here, after all. It brings back really warm memories of 239-style writing. There you go, I said it – you did resurrect that feeling, hat’s off to your brilliant team.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Like&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;idea&nbsp;behind&nbsp;Dr.&nbsp;Dan&nbsp;and&nbsp;major&nbsp;Wilford.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Like&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;idea&nbsp;behind&nbsp;Dr.&nbsp;Dan&nbsp;and&nbsp;goddamn&nbsp;Bowe.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Which is the philosophy of Secure, Contain, Protect over again. When to do what? Do we continue to use anomalies? Thanks to this whole story, Alpha-9 basically made its point now. And I don’t know about Dan making excuses for Wilford, after 10 years of waiting for death, jee golly, Dan is a real tough guy and should be taken to Dr Glass for psych evaluation. General Bowe, on the other hand, turned out to be a great villainous warmonger with a justified goal. Kinda reminded me of Colonel Miles Quaritch in 2009 Avatar.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Alpha-9&nbsp;itself,&nbsp;unfortunately,&nbsp;has&nbsp;gone&nbsp;by&nbsp;the&nbsp;wayside.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Alpha-9&nbsp;itself,&nbsp;unfortunately,&nbsp;has&nbsp;gone&nbsp;by&nbsp;the&nbsp;wayside.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Which is understandable, most of the writers for main Resurrection have moved on with some things else (fuck that is disappointing). I did like that you carried on the roles of Dr. Light, Iris, Adams, Dr. Clef, Dr. Crow, but Alpha-9 is not only about them. The subtle mentions of Clef still being a professional, charismatic dick, but a little warmer towards his protegee, Adams, was great, but it somehow lacked his charisma. Kain Pathos Crow’s role made a good impression. Sure, I would’ve liked to see Crow in SCP-244-ARC, or his collaboration with a Brain in a Jar about the Olympia project, but without those – his stealth-hound role was both hilarious and respectful.<br />
Some of the characters from Alpha-9 have not had their say:<br />
- Alexander Foxx’s role has been depicted profoundly, and he would have been great in subterfuge;<br />
- Alexandra’s AI capability would have been invaluable in combat and a satisfactory AIAD reference;<br />
- Dr. Gears could have been a great mentor for the burning, enthusiastic and exhausted Dan. Or as an outsider of Alpha-9, an interesting liaison to O5s;<br />
- Dr. Bright, Dr. Bridge and Dr. Dietrich, agent Lurk, Chelsea Elliott, SCPs 073, 985, 1985, 2599, 2913… the list is huge. Of course, one cannot incorporate all of them, being a group of 4 authors, no matter how good, in such a short time.<br />
Here’s hoping that we see more of them in the future. I love most of them, and I have joined the Foundation as a translator because of these interesting, well-written characters.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;The&nbsp;O5s&nbsp;suck.&nbsp;In&nbsp;storytelling&nbsp;the&nbsp;almighty&nbsp;always&nbsp;do.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;The&nbsp;O5s&nbsp;suck.&nbsp;In&nbsp;storytelling&nbsp;the&nbsp;almighty&nbsp;always&nbsp;do.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Their power is immense, but their actions in time of a huge crisis are less than poor. I find that a little unbelievable. They are truly caught with their pants down, and that is not something you would expect from <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/the-high-court-with-the-magic-army">the High Court</a>, or at least O5-13, the future-seer. I’m sure there are ways to cloud their vision or otherwise justify their weakness, and it would have been great to see these.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
All in all, you did a super great job in a short time. You resurrected and expanded that tone of 239 and Duke till Dawn, which is what this is all about. I would very much you to contact the authors of the original Resurrection to fill in the gaps and make a big update for the Hub. The place for your stories there is well-deserved.
							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>&quot;Тень улыбки промелькнула на бледном, без кровинки, лице Боромира.&quot; - Перевод Н. Григорьевой, В. Грушецкого.<br />
&quot;Boromir smiled.&quot; - J.R.R. Tolkien</p>

				</div>
					
					
