		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4810156)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4810156">
																		Re: +1
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/harryblank" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6479803); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6479803&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610224711" alt="HarryBlank" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6479803)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/harryblank" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6479803); return false;" >HarryBlank</a></span> <span class="odate time_1604373028 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Nov 2020 03:10</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4810156">
									

<p>Wow, I'm really glad you liked what we did! And thanks for those detailed notes, it makes the whole process even more worthwhile than it already was.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Harry's&nbsp;thoughts</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Escape&nbsp;Harry's&nbsp;thoughts</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The skips: I looked up every single article on the entire site that uses Site-19 and vetted them for weaponizability. Every single one. The ones which stayed were the ones I had the most fun with; there's a few deleted scenes with more, because although it might not be apparent to everyone, I <em>did</em> exercise some restraint :P</p>
<p>The whiteboards: that was one of my first ideas for the overall story of the Bowe Decom tales, and I was super excited about it. Glad it landed.</p>
<p>I think I'll employ Cassy further, I have an idea about that.</p>
<p>I wanted us to move the story forward without stepping on the toes of the original writers, who presumably want to continue their stuff at some point. Justifying A9 seemed like a good permanent consequence that shouldn't get in the way of what the OG Resurrectors want to do.</p>
<p>That's also why there's less use of the main Res characters here; we did a sort of side story which expands the universe but doesn't delimit other people's options. I've got ideas for most of the Res characters, but I trust the people who crafted the original storylines to see them through to their desired conclusions eventually.</p>
<p>not_a_seagull took Bowe and ran with him. Terrific job, like all my team members.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Hope to expand on the backstory and introduce some more frontstory, because this has been just so much fun you have no idea. Thank you for the kind words and support :)</p>
<p>Let me echo Pighead's comment above: read New Faces! It's very good, and should scratch your O5 shenanigans itch.</p>

							</div>

								
